%description
The strided iterator adapts multidimensional buffers to work with the C++
standard library and range-based for-loops. Given a pointer or iterator
into a multidimensional data buffer, one can generate an iterator range
using make_strided to construct strided versions of the standard library's
begin and end. For constructing range-based for-loops, a strided_range
class is provided. These help authors to avoid integer-based indexing,
which in some cases can impede algorithm performance and introduce
indexing errors. This library exists primarily to expose the header file
to other R projects.

